citations:
    citation-affc-jaime-iii:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Jaime III"
            text_from_source: "The fields outside the walls of Darry were being tilled once more."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Jaime's column arrives at Darry Castle. He finds Lancel Lannister (now lord of Darry by marriage to Lady Amerei, a half-Darry) has become intensely religious and intends to abandon his lordship and wife to join the Warrior's Sons. Jaime confronts Lancel in the sept, where Lancel confesses to having slept with Cersei and (tacitly) to helping poison King Robert. Lady Amerei's mother Lady Mariya Frey tells Jaime of a hooded woman leading the Brotherhood Without Banners after Merrett Frey's death — hinting at Lady Stoneheart."
